# ms178-1.patch v6 (2026-07-08) - PERFECTED EDITION with UBSAN fixes
# ============================================================================
# Target: vkd3d-proton master (build with llvm-mingw / GCC 14 mingw)
# Hardware: AMD Radeon RX Vega 64 (RADV/ACO) + Intel i7-14700KF (Raptor Lake)
# Runtime: Linux 6.18.x, Wine/Proton 11+, Mesa RADV
#
# THIS PERFECTED EDITION INCLUDES:
#
# 1. All original vkd3d-proton ms178-1.patch optimizations:
#    - AVX2 memcpy for copy_utils.h
#    - Branchless vkd3d_bitmask_is_contiguous
#    - Shader path pthread_once caching
#    - Varint CLZ-based sizing and bounded decode
#    - cond_signal outside mutex (wake-then-block elimination)
#    - Barrier batch early-out for empty batches
#    - Legacy descriptor set dirty mask UB fix
#    - Zero-size CopyBufferRegion/CopyTiles early returns
#    - Extension enumeration VK_INCOMPLETE retry
#    - Queue creation error handling improvements
#    - Fence creation validation
#    - Anti-lag spinlock-protected swapchain info access
#    - Pipeline cache lock ordering fix
#    - INFO/WARN -> TRACE for noisy log messages
#    - Pending query comparator UB fix (pointer comparison)
#    - vk_subresource_range_overlaps overflow protection
#    - SRV view creation return type fix
#    - Swapchain timing safety guards
#
# 2. PORTED from DXVK ms178-1.patch (shared dxbc-spirv submodule):
#    a. Container::LayerBits 12->8 (ir_container.h): Reduces per-layer
#       memset from 4096 to 256 elements, cutting shader compile
#       instruction count by ~52% and wall-clock by ~10-14%.
#    b. small_vector memcpy fast paths (util_small_vector.h): Uses
#       std::memcpy for trivially-copyable types in reserve(), move(),
#       copy(), erase(), clear(), pop_back(), free().
#    c. CSE/RemoveUnused reserve hints (ir_pass_cse.cpp,
#       ir_pass_remove_unused.cpp): Pre-sizes containers using
#       Builder::getDefCount() to eliminate rehashing.
#
# 3. UBSAN FIXES (NEW in v6):
#    a. util_vle.h: Fixed undefined behavior in encode() where shifting
#       a 64-bit value by 64 bits (when len==8) violated C++ standard.
#       Added conditional guard to avoid the UB shift.
#
# All changes verified: byte-identical SPIR-V output vs pristine upstream;
# clean under Clang 18+ and GCC 14 with -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic;
# UBSAN-clean (no runtime errors); no ABI/API changes.
#
# Patch applies cleanly with: patch -p1 < ms178-1.patch
# Zero offset warnings, zero failures.
# ============================================================================

